#E7 -> Carbon Sequestration  --> Text update --> final_design_certificate
SchemeCriterionText.find_by(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Parks", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:final_design_certificate], renovation:false)), name: "Carbon Sequestration"), name: "PURPOSE", display_weight: 2, visible: true).update(html_text: "<p>To remove carbon dioxide from the atmosphere and store carbon in vegetation and soil through urban green space.</p>", display_weight: 1)
SchemeCriterionText.find_by(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Parks", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:final_design_certificate], renovation:false)), name: "Carbon Sequestration"), name: "ASSESSMENT PRINCIPLES", display_weight: 3, visible: true).update(html_text: "<ul><li>The Project will <span>assess</span> the methodology, inventory and estimation of carbon stocks in the living biomass in the constructed park.</li><li>The The Project will submit a Carbon Sequestration <span>Plan</span> to establish the <span>criterion level</span>.</li></ul>", display_weight: 2)
SchemeCriterionText.find_by(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Parks", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], certification_type: Certificate.certification_types[:final_design_certificate], renovation:false)), name: "Carbon Sequestration"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 4, visible: true).update(html_text: "<p>The criterion requires assessing the quantity of organic carbon that can be stored in the living biomass of the constructed park.  The amount of carbon sequestered from plants can be determined through crown cover and growth rate. The crown cover area method should be used when data is available on the total area of tree crown cover, whereas the tree growth rate method should be used where data on the number of trees by broad species class is available.</p> <p>Clean Development Mechanism AR-Tool-14 shall be used for estimation of carbon stock and change in carbon stock in living biomass of trees and shrubs in an afforestation and reforestation project activity. The tool considers the ex-ante estimation (projection) for the estimation of carbon stock. The computation for the emission reduction shall be undertaken through the estimation by proportionate cover. Refer to GSAS 2019 Parks Guidelines Manual and the Clean Development Mechanism AR-Tool-14 document for further details.</p> <p>The carbon sequestration plan is a comprehensive document that outlines the carbon sequestration methodology or protocol that is specific to the type of offset project generating the reductions.</p> <p>The plan demonstrates the following requirements:</p> <ul><li>Description of project activity.</li><li>Application of selected methodologies.</li><li>Estimation of emission reductions.</li><li>Monitoring plan.</li><li>Start date, crediting period type and duration.</li></ul> <p>The criterion level is established based on the degree of compliance of the plan to the requirements of E.7 Carbon Sequestration.</p>", display_weight: 3)
